  "language": "en",
  "text": "How did you get rich? You see all these buildings around here? Yes. So far, year to date, we've done $6 billion in real estate sales. So you're in the real estate business? Very much so. How many billionaires have you met today? 101. You keep a list of them? Absolutely. It's my job. It's my number one job. What is your best networking advice for anybody in business? Every room I go into, I use the two C's. You give someone a compliment and you find something in common. Once you get their contact info, you follow up with them within 10 minutes. I send them a quick note, a quick text. So great meeting you seven and a half minutes ago. Let's do something great together. I keep it unread and then I follow up until they buy or I fucking die. That's how you do it. I try to meet somewhere between five and 15 new people every single day. Give me $6 billion worth of sales advice right here. The simplest idea, which is the hardest to understand is that people hate being sold, but they love shopping with friends. Your number one job as a salesperson is to create relationships. It's not to sell product. I don't think I ever actually sell apartments or sell buildings. I just sold something in Palm Beach, all combined for $308 million. Over the phone, had nothing to do with anything other than the trust and the relationship that I was able to create between a person who wanted to buy and a person who wanted to sell. How do you know? I'm 41. Ryan, if me and you died tomorrow and you had one last message to leave with the younger generation, what would that be? One of the best pieces of advice that I've been given from my most successful and wealthiest billionaire clients is that most people are in a race against time. Time is their greatest asset. The wealthiest people are in a race against moments. I'd love that. I'd rather regret the things I did than the things I never tried. So, take the risk or lose the chance. Of course. You got amazing advice, brother. Thank you so much for your time. I appreciate you coming.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 0.7,
      "text": "How did you get rich?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.1,
      "end": 2.3,
      "text": "You see all these buildings around here?"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.5,
      "end": 2.7,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 2.9,
      "end": 5.1,
      "text": "So far, year to date, we've done $6 billion"
    },
    {
      "start": 5.4,
      "end": 6.3,
      "text": "in real estate sales."
    },
    {
      "start": 6.5,
      "end": 7.4,
      "text": "So you're in the real estate business?"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.7,
      "end": 8.4,
      "text": "Very much so."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.5,
      "end": 9.8,
      "text": "How many billionaires have you met today?"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.1,
      "end": 10.4,
      "text": "101."
    },
    {
      "start": 11.4,
      "end": 12.2,
      "text": "You keep a list of them?"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.4,
      "end": 12.8,
      "text": "Absolutely."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.4,
      "end": 14.3,
      "text": "It's my job."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.6,
      "end": 16.2,
      "text": "It's my number one job."
    },
    {
      "start": 16.4,
      "end": 17.8,
      "text": "What is your best networking advice"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.8,
      "end": 18.7,
      "text": "for anybody in business?"
    },
    {
      "start": 19.0,
      "end": 21.4,
      "text": "Every room I go into, I use the two C's."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.6,
      "end": 22.5,
      "text": "You give someone a compliment"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.5,
      "end": 23.9,
      "text": "and you find something in common."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.1,
      "end": 25.3,
      "text": "Once you get their contact info,"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.5,
